Tottenham made an enquiry for Napoli striker Victor Osimhen in January, Football Insider understands. But the Serie A club knocked back the approach from Spurs for the 23-year-old as they looked to sign an attacker in the recent window. A recruitment source has told Football Insider that Tottenham plan to return again for Osimhen in the summer.   BROTHERS AT WAR: Salah, Mane set for AFCON final showdown     IOC faults FIFA over  proposed biennial World     Dangote visits revamped Moshood Abiola Stadium   He is valued at around the £70million mark by Napoli after signing in the summer of 2020 in a part-exchange deal that valued him then at around the £30m mark. An A-list new striker is a key target of the Londoners going into the main window regardless of Harry Kane’s future. Antonio Conte often plays two strikers in his favoured 3-5-2 formation and wants top quality cover and competition for main stars Kane and Son Heung-Min. - Advertisement - Osimhen fits into that category after establishing himself in Serie A and Ligue 1 as well as in the Europa League and at international level for Nigeria. The front man has netted nine goals from 18 matches in all competitions this season, during which he has missed two months with a fractured cheekbone.